title: Ireland Appears Set to Legalize Same-Sex Marriage
description: Opinion polls and high turnout in urban areas favored a yes vote on the referendum, which would make Ireland the first nation to approve same-sex marriage by popular vote.

title: Senate Blocks Bill on N.S.A. Collection of Phone Records
description: The Senate voted 57-42, short of the 60 votes needed to move ahead on a House bill that would have ended the National Security Agency’s bulk collection of domestic phone records.

title: Rangers 5, Lightning 1: Same Characters, Improved Script as Rangers Crush Lightning
description: Rick Nash scored two goals, Martin St. Louis added one and Tampa Bay’s dangerous first line did not score as the Rangers knotted the Eastern Conference finals, 2-2.

title: Senate Vote Is a Victory for Obama on Trade, but a Tougher Test Awaits
description: Senator Mitch McConnell aligned with the president to push the deal, which would link 12 nations on either side of the Pacific into a trading bloc and expand the president’s trading authority. The legislation still requires House approval.

title: Honor Comes Late to Óscar Romero, a Martyr for the Poor
description: Pope Francis’ decision to beatify Óscar Romero, the Salvadoran archbishop who was killed in 1980, is widely seen as a recognition of the deep pastoral commitment the archbishop demonstrated.

title: Marques Haynes, 89, Dies; Dribbled as a Globetrotter and Dazzled Worldwide
description: Haynes was a stellar cog on the Globetrotter squads of the late 1940s and early ’50s, and was later inducted into the Naismith Basketball Hall of Fame.

title: U.S. Flies Over a Chinese Project at Sea, and Beijing Objects
description: The Chinese are unhappy that the U.S. Navy is watching a huge reclamation project to turn reefs into islands in the Spratly Islands, a group of reefs in the South China Sea.

title: Obama Stresses Support for Israel, but Refuses to ‘Paper Over’ Discord
description: President Obama used a speech to knock down perceptions, fueled in part by recent tussles over Iran, that he lacks a commitment to Israelis and Jewish concerns.

title: Drop That Nozzle: New Jersey Resists Push for Self-Service at the Gas Pump
description: For 70 years, New Jersey has banned self-serve gas stations and most residents want it to stay that way.

title: More Than One Attacker Is Suspected in Killings of 4 in Washington
description: Investigators said Darron D. Wint, charged in the killings of four people, stayed ahead of a police search with aid from others.

title: 40 Are Killed in Gun Battle in Mexico
description: Most of the dead were civilians in a confrontation after the ambush of a police convoy in an area known for drug gangs bordering Michoacán and Jalisco States.

title: G.O.P. Candidates Take Tougher Tone at Forum
description: In Oklahoma City, Republican presidential hopefuls — including Jeb Bush and Govs. Scott Walker and Chris Christie — moved to contrast themselves with others in the field.

title: Pakistan Widens Inquiry Into Fake Diplomas
description: Heavy scrutiny has mounted over the past week for Axact, a Karachi-based software company that has made millions selling fake degrees through a sprawling empire of school websites.

title: More Than One Attacker Is Suspected in Killings of 4 in Washington
description: Investigators said Daron D. Wint, charged in the killings of four people, stayed ahead of a weeklong police search with the aid of a number of people.

title: Farmers Agree to Water Cuts in California
description: State officials accepted an offer from growers in the Sacramento-San Joaquin River Delta to give up a quarter of their water this season.

title: G.M. Inquiry Said to Find Criminal Wrongdoing
description: As the investigation draws to a close, prosecutors are said to be negotiating a penalty that is likely to eclipse the $1.2 billion paid last year by Toyota.

title: ArtsBeat: TLC Pulls ‘19 Kids and Counting’ From Its Lineup
description: The show was removed following allegations that one of the show’s stars, Josh Duggar, had previously been investigated for molesting several minors.

title: A Hillary Clinton Match-Up With Marco Rubio Is a Scary Thought for Democrats
description: They are worried that Mr. Rubio, a son of Cuban immigrants, could win over Hispanic voters and that he would offer a sharp generational contrast.

title: For One Irish Couple, Backing Gay Marriage Is a Matter of Family Values
description: Brighid and Paddy Whyte are Catholic and have been married nearly 50 years. They made a video to encourage Irish voters to support gay marriage, and it went viral.

title: New Trial Expected for Man Convicted in Chandra Levy Death
description: A man convicted of killing Washington intern Chandra Levy is expected to get a new trial after government attorneys withdrew their opposition to one.
